==English==

===Etymology 1===
Noun from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|wund|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*wundō}}. Verb from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|wundian|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*wundōną}}. Indo-European cognates include Albanian {{term|unë||piece of a broken pot, splinter|lang=sq}}.

